Hello lovely people,

I have a question for you. During our meetups, we’ve primarily focused on speaking, and I truly believe that many—if not all—of you have significantly improved your speaking abilities thanks to our sessions.

However, as you may have already noticed, we haven’t incorporated much grammar practice into our meetups so far. I’ve been wondering how we could best include it in a way that’s both helpful and engaging.

One idea I had is to create a grammar quiz that would test your knowledge based on the most common mistakes I’ve observed during our meetups. Using the quiz results, I could then design occasional custom lessons specifically addressing these common grammar challenges.

I’d love to hear your thoughts on this approach. If you like it please leave a like!



